<article>

<title>OpenMap Viewer Application
<author>BBN Technologies
<date>1 December 1998
<abstract>
This document is a user's guide for running the OpenMap Viewer
application.  It assumes that you have already built and installed the
OpenMap package.
</abstract>


<toc>
<p>
The OpenMap Viewer application is our basic MapViewer application.  It
allows you to add, remove, and change the positioning of different
layers on the map, and to navigate over the map.  There are many other
applications that use the OpenMap components.  We encourage you to try
out the Viewer and to tweak it to fit your own needs.


<sect>Launch Scripts
<p>
We've included launch scripts for UNIX and Windows in the
<tt>bin/</tt> subdirectory of the installation.  They are
<tt>openmap</tt> and <tt>openmap.bat</tt>.  If you're running on
Windows, you may need to edit the paths referenced in the
<tt>openmap.bat</tt> script.  These scripts set your
<tt>CLASSPATH</tt> before invoking the Java VM.
<p>


<sect>Properties File
<p>
The OpenMap Viewer loads properties from an
<tt>openmap.properties</tt> file.  It searches for this file in three
locations: 1) in the JAR file or class directory, 2) in the
installation "share" subdirectory, and 3) in the user's home
directory.  If it finds the file in any of these places, it loads the
properties from it, overriding previous settings.  We suggest that you
copy the <tt>openmap.properties</tt> file from the installation
"share" subdirectory to your home directory, and edit the settings to
your own liking.


